Thank you for your request for information regarding our company’s corporate compliance policies. Please find below a high-level overview of our key policy areas. If you require the full, detailed policy documents or any additional information, kindly let me know and I will forward them promptly.

1. Code of Conduct
   • Establishes ethical standards for all employees, officers and directors.
   • Covers conflicts of interest, gifts & hospitality, anti-discrimination and reporting obligations.

2. Anti-Bribery & Anti-Corruption (ABAC) Policy
   • Zero-tolerance stance on bribery or facilitation payments.
   • Mandatory due diligence on third-party intermediaries and government interactions.

3. Whistleblower & Non-Retaliation Policy
   • Confidential, toll-free hotline and online portal managed by an independent vendor.
   • Protects whistleblowers from retaliation and provides investigation timelines.

4. Data Privacy & Security Policy
   • Aligns with GDPR, CCPA and other applicable regulations.
   • Defines data classification, access controls and breach-notification procedures.

5. Trade Compliance & Sanctions Policy
   • Screening processes for customers and suppliers against restricted party lists.
   • Internal licensing review workflow for controlled technology or exports.

6. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) & Know-Your-Customer (KYC) Program
   • Risk-based customer due-diligence and enhanced due-diligence for high-risk clients.
   • Ongoing transaction monitoring and suspicious activity reporting.

7. Compliance Training & Certification
   • Annual mandatory e-learning modules and live workshops for high-risk functions.
   • Completion tracking and escalation for overdue training.

8. Monitoring, Auditing & Continuous Improvement
   • Internal audits performed at least annually.
   • Corrective action tracking and quarterly Compliance Committee review.

We continually review and update these policies to ensure alignment with current laws, regulations, and best practices.

